# Define seed value, X and y
seed = 7
split_seed = 612

X = patients_final.drop(['Outcome'], axis=1)
y = patients_final['Outcome']

scale_pos_weight = y.value_counts()[0] / float(y.value_counts()[1])
In [4]:
# Define training and heldout datasets
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.model_selection import RepeatedKFold, StratifiedKFold

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=split_seed, stratify=y)

skf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=4, random_state=seed)
rkf = RepeatedKFold(n_splits=4, n_repeats=10, random_state=seed)

from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer

index = X_train.index
X_train = SimpleImputer().fit_transform(X_train)
X_train = pd.DataFrame(X_train, columns=X.columns, index=index)
index = X_test.index
X_test = SimpleImputer().fit_transform(X_test)
X_test = pd.DataFrame(X_test, columns=X.columns, index=index)

import shap
explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(model)
shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_train)

test_shap_values = explainer.shap_values(X_test)


# shap.dependence_plot("Op_PCI_success", shap_values, X_train)
top_inds = np.argsort(-np.sum(np.abs(test_shap_values), 0))

# make SHAP plots of the three most important features
for i in range(20):
    shap.dependence_plot(top_inds[i], test_shap_values, X_test)# make SHAP plots of the three most important features
for i in range(20):
    shap.dependence_plot(top_inds[i], shap_values, X_train)
